					<description><![CDATA[<p>ZutaCore Raises Major Funding for AI Infrastructure Growth ZutaCore raised 100 million in a series C funding round. Mitsubishi Electric, Carrier Ventures, Samsung Ventures along with some other investors had</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/zutacore-raises-100m-ai-cooling-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">ZutaCore Raises $100M to Expand Waterless AI Cooling Technology</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>ZutaCore Raises Major Funding for AI Infrastructure Growth</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">ZutaCore raised 100 million in a series C funding round. Mitsubishi Electric, Carrier Ventures, Samsung Ventures along with some other investors had contributed to this investment round. This investment comes at an apex stage of boom in artificial intelligence infrastructure as there is a massive demand across global data centers for sophisticated cooling solutions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company which is located in California manufactures waterless liquid cooling solutions for AI and HPC workloads that cater to the demanding processors. Modern AI systems generate tremendous amounts of heat and using conventional cooling mechanisms has become a great challenge to escalate at par.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company states that the new funds would facilitate their commercial growth and scale its operations and increase its global footprint in critical markets as well as customer installations will be improved and R&amp;D would continue to be the high priority area.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors feel that with this new technology, these advanced cooling solutions will be one of the key elements in the coming time of AI computing. The data centers have a lot of pressure to optimize efficiency and with the increasing need for powerful processors there is always an increased need of more efficient cooling mechanisms to handle the immense processing power of AI machines.</span></p>
<h2><b>Waterless Cooling Platform Targets Next-Generation AI Chips</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">At the centre of ZutaCore’s business is its HyperCool platform. The system uses a waterless two-phase cooling process. A specialised dielectric fluid absorbs processor heat through boiling. The heat is then removed through condensation before the fluid circulates again.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This closed-loop approach eliminates water inside the data hall. The design reduces operational risks associated with traditional water-based cooling systems. It also improves energy efficiency. According to the company, data centre energy consumption can be reduced by as much as 82 percent.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The technology has become increasingly relevant because of rising AI workloads. New processor architectures require far greater thermal management capabilities. Many next-generation chips are expected to exceed 4,000 watts. Existing cooling approaches often struggle under these conditions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">ZutaCore continues to develop products for future computing requirements. Its OmniTherm cold plate was designed to support advanced NVIDIA Blackwell server architectures. The solution enables full-power operation in demanding enterprise environments. This positions the company to benefit from expanding AI infrastructure investment.</span></p>
<h2><b>Global Deployments Demonstrate Growing Market Adoption</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202271" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202271" class="size-full wp-image-202271" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-with_a7B5F7gXW4ebOjpHaJil0g_CrTr975eQgGutosJGup_-A.png" alt="Global AI data centers with advanced cooling systems and thermal testing facility." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202271" class="wp-caption-text">ZutaCore expands global deployments as demand rises for scalable AI cooling solutions. Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has already completed more than 75 deployments worldwide. These projects span North America, Europe, and Asia. The growing deployment count highlights increasing customer confidence. It also demonstrates broader acceptance of liquid cooling technology.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">AI infrastructure operators are searching for scalable thermal solutions. Processor densities continue to rise rapidly. Traditional air cooling methods are reaching practical limitations. This shift is creating opportunities for alternative technologies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To support future deployments, ZutaCore established a 2MW End-of-Row thermal emulation platform in Israel. The facility replicates real-world operating conditions. Customers can evaluate performance before implementation. This process reduces deployment risk and improves system reliability.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company also collaborates with global technology partners. These partnerships support product integration and market expansion. Industry demand continues to accelerate. As a result, ZutaCore expects deployment activity to increase significantly over the coming years.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/factorial-raises-150m-ai-workforce-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Factorial Raises $150M to Expand AI Workforce Platform Across Europe</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Leadership Expansion Supports Commercialisation Strategy</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">ZutaCore is strengthening its leadership team alongside its growth plans. Several senior executives recently joined the company. These appointments are intended to support international expansion. They will also help manage larger customer deployments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Yaniv Reinhold joined as Chief Financial Officer. Sarah Warshavsky Oberman became Chief People Officer. Yoni Nir assumed the role of Chief Research and Development Officer. Sharon Shafran was appointed Chief Operating Officer.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">These executives bring extensive experience from global technology companies. Their expertise covers finance, operations, engineering, </span><a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/social-sciences/talent-management" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">talent management</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, and product development. The company believes strong leadership will be essential during its next growth phase. Expansion requires both operational discipline and technical innovation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Chairman and Chief Executive Officer Erez Freibach said the funding validates market demand for the company’s technology. He noted that AI is reshaping data centre infrastructure globally. Existing approaches are becoming insufficient for future computing needs. ZutaCore aims to provide a scalable alternative.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company enters this next stage with significant momentum. Customer adoption continues to increase. Product development remains active. With fresh capital and growing market demand, ZutaCore is positioning itself as a key player in the future of AI infrastructure cooling.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/zutacore-raises-100m-ai-cooling-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">ZutaCore Raises $100M to Expand Waterless AI Cooling Technology</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
