					<description><![CDATA[<p>Factorial Raises Major Funding to Accelerate AI Strategy Factorial raised a $150 million Series D round at a valuation of $2.5 billion. The round was led by General Catalyst and</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/factorial-raises-150m-ai-workforce-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal">Factorial Raises $150M to Expand AI Workforce Platform Across Europe</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Factorial Raises Major Funding to Accelerate AI Strategy</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Factorial raised a $150 million Series D round at a valuation of $2.5 billion. The round was led by General Catalyst and supported by its previous investors Atomico and Four Rivers. The investment now positions Factorial as one of Europe’s biggest AI scale-ups. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Initially launched in Barcelona in 2016 to specialize in HR software targeting small-medium businesses, today Factorial has over 16,000 customers worldwide in over 90 countries. The fundraise signals increasing investor faith inFactorial’spivot. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has spent the last year rebuilding its entire platform on artificial intelligence in a belief that the technology will fundamentally transform how businesses operate, a perspective it seems to have shared with investors. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">General Catalyst has made its first direct investment in Factorial via the round, believing it to be a perfect example of what leading AI-enabled enterprise software businesses look like. The firm’s partners suggest that the next leaders of the software market will be building from scratch with AI, not adding a couple of features to existing products.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Workforce Platform Drives Company Transformation</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Factorial’s growth story now centres on its AI-first strategy. Chief Executive Officer Jordi Romero said the company has fundamentally changed its approach. The platform has been redesigned to operate around intelligent agents. These agents help automate tasks across business functions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">At the centre of this strategy is Factorial One. The platform uses a simplified two-agent model. One agent represents the organisation. The second represents the employee.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This structure differs from competitors deploying large numbers of specialised agents. Factorial believes businesses want fewer systems. It also believes organisations value accountability and simplicity. The company argues that a unified approach improves efficiency.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform now supports workflows across HR, finance and IT operations. It learns company policies over time. It can execute routine tasks automatically. It also adapts to changing business requirements. This shift allows Factorial to target a larger software market.</span></p>
<h2><b>General Catalyst Adds $540M Growth Commitment<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202261" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202261" class="size-full wp-image-202261" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-with_S07-_LFvVEiK64sLPJ0emg_GoT4W4ydSQ6Ko7LqWfHcrQ.png" alt="AI enterprise platform with financial growth network and customer value metrics." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202261" class="wp-caption-text">Factorial expands with flexible capital strategy tied to customer value and long-term growth. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The equity funding was only part of the announcement. General Catalyst also committed up to $540 million through its Customer Value Fund. This brings total available capital to more than $700 million. General Catalyst believes Factorial has built a strong foundation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Customer Value Fund uses a different financing structure. Returns are linked to customer value creation. They are not tied directly to additional equity ownership. This allows companies to fund growth without significant dilution.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">For Factorial, the structure provides flexibility. The company can invest heavily in customer acquisition. It can also preserve ownership for existing </span><a href="https://www.investopedia.com/terms/s/shareholder.asp" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">shareholders</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. This approach supports long-term expansion plans.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The commitment reflects confidence in Factorial’s business model. The company has demonstrated strong recurring revenue performance. It has also shown disciplined financial management during its growth journey. These factors helped strengthen investor conviction.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company combines product innovation with operational discipline. That combination attracted both equity investment and additional financing support. The partnership is expected to support growth for several years.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/mach-industries-raises-300-million-defence/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Mach Industries Raises $300 Million to Scale Advanced Defence Systems</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Germany Becomes Key Target for European Expansion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A significant portion of the new capital will be invested in Germany. Factorial considers Germany its most important international market. The company plans to establish a new office in Munich. The location will serve as a regional growth hub.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Germany offers a large opportunity for workforce software providers. Older systems are common for many medium-sized companies. Factorial&#8217;s AI platform should overcome such issues. The company intends to grow its market share fast.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Hiring is expected to grow a lot in the coming year. The company intends to hire people in sales, customer success, engineering and marketing. They will also hire people for product development. The management expects hiring to stay quite intense.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In addition to Germany, Factorial will grow more in Europe. France, Italy and Portugal are still important growth markets and all have a very strong adoption. Management intends to reinforce local operations there.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">They are currently around 2,600 employees worldwide and are still growing quickly. Management indicates they are hiring around 50 employees a week despite current difficulties. Continued investment will support this momentum.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Factorial’s latest funding round highlights broader changes within European technology markets. Investors increasingly favour companies applying AI to practical business problems. Rather than focusing solely on infrastructure providers, capital is flowing into software firms delivering measurable productivity gains.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s valuation reflects those expectations. Whether it can sustain that position will depend on execution. Continued customer growth will remain critical. Successful expansion across Europe will also play an important role.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Factorial enters its next stage with substantial financial backing. It also enters with ambitious plans for AI-led growth. Investors are betting that the company can redefine workforce management. The coming years will determine whether that vision becomes reality.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
