					<description><![CDATA[<p>Contraline Raises $92.5 Million to Advance Male Contraceptive Development Contraline has raised $92.5 million in a Series B financing round. The round was co-led by BVF Partners and RA Capital</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/contraline-raises-92-5m/" data-wpel-link="internal">Contraline Raises $92.5 Million Series B to Advance NES/T Male Contraceptive Development</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Contraline Raises $92.5 Million to Advance Male Contraceptive Development</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Contraline has raised $92.5 million in a Series B financing round. The round was co-led by BVF Partners and RA Capital Management. It also included participation from GV, Lumira Ventures, Invus, and other investors. The capital will support late-stage development of NES/T Gel.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NES/T Gel is a hormonal male contraceptive candidate designed for daily use. It is applied as a topical gel to suppress sperm production. The formulation maintains physiological testosterone levels in users. This balance is central to its safety approach.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company plans to use the funding to advance Phase 3 readiness. It will also support regulatory preparation and manufacturing scale-up. Contraline aims to expand reproductive options for men and couples. The focus is on both hormonal and non-hormonal innovation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This funding marks a major step for the company’s clinical pipeline. It strengthens execution capacity for late-stage trials. It also supports long-term development strategy. The company is positioning for global reproductive health expansion.</span></p>
<h2><b>NES/T Gel Shows Positive Phase 2b Clinical Results</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NES/T Gel recently completed a global Phase 2b clinical trial. The study enrolled 462 couples across multiple regions. It evaluated safety, efficacy, and user acceptability outcomes. The results showed encouraging contraceptive performance.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The treatment also demonstrated reversibility after discontinuation. Participants returned to baseline fertility after stopping use. Tolerability results were reported as strong. This supports its potential for long-term use.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The therapy combines segesterone acetate and testosterone. Segesterone acetate suppresses sperm production effectively. Testosterone maintains normal hormonal function in users. This dual approach reduces hormonal imbalance risks.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Contraline believes this mechanism addresses a major gap. Current male contraceptive options are limited. Condoms and vasectomy remain the primary methods. No approved drug-based alternatives exist today.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company expects Phase 3 trials to begin in 2027. NES/T is positioned as a potential first pharmacologic male contraceptive. It was originally developed with academic research partners. Contraline now holds global rights for development and commercialisation.</span></p>
<h2><b>Investor Confidence and Expansion of Male Health Pipeline<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202234" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202234" class="size-full wp-image-202234" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-elem_qshOWafRXJWlhmtp2gI5BQ_EFWfnGBXReqJ7crKOTFrsg_cover.png" alt="Male contraceptive innovation with biotech systems and clinical pipeline development." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202234" class="wp-caption-text">Contraline strengthens its pipeline with investor backing and dual contraceptive innovation. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Series B financing attracted major healthcare investors. BVF Partners and RA Capital co-led the round. GV, Lumira Ventures, Invus, and others also participated. The deal reflects strong investor confidence.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A board appointment was made alongside the financing. Iris van Alderwerelt van Rosenburgh joins from BVF Partners. This strengthens governance and strategic oversight. It supports long-term clinical development planning.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors see male contraception as a large unmet market. Existing options remain limited to condoms and vasectomy. No approved pharmaceutical solutions are available. This creates a significant innovation gap.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Contraline is also advancing ADAM, a non-hormonal implant. It is designed for long-acting reversible contraception. The programme complements NES/T development. It expands the company’s pipeline approach.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">ADAM is expected to enter Phase 2 trials next year. It targets multi-year contraceptive protection for men. The company aims to build a diversified portfolio. It focuses on both hormonal and non-hormonal pathways.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Contraline’s long-term strategy targets leadership in male reproductive health. It aims to scale across multiple clinical programmes. It is building a broad innovation platform. The goal is category leadership in male contraception.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/highland-electric-fleets-raises-75-million/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Highland Electric Fleets Raises $75 Million to Scale Electric School Bus Expansion</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Market Demand and Long-Term Development Strategy</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Contraline highlights rising global demand for male contraception. It estimates over 40 million men in the US may consider use. This signals strong unmet healthcare demand. It also reflects changing social attitudes.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Male contraception remains limited in modern healthcare systems. Current options are restricted to condoms and vasectomy. No approved drug-based alternatives exist yet. This highlights a major treatment gap.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Scientific challenges have slowed development historically. Sperm suppression requires high safety standards in healthy users. This increases regulatory complexity significantly. It has slowed pharmaceutical progress.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Funding constraints have also limited innovation. </span><a href="https://www.who.int/health-topics/contraception" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Contraception</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> has received lower investment historically. This has delayed large-scale clinical development. Other therapeutic areas have progressed faster.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Healthcare behaviour is now shifting globally. Telehealth platforms are increasing male engagement in care. This supports broader acceptance of reproductive health solutions. It improves access and awareness.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NES/T aims to address these challenges directly. It maintains testosterone levels while suppressing sperm production. This improves tolerability and usability outcomes. It is designed for daily administration. The Series B funding supports full Phase 3 preparation. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It also strengthens manufacturing and regulatory planning. Contraline is preparing for late-stage execution. It is building clinical and operational readiness. The company continues a dual-pipeline strategy.  NES/T represents its hormonal approach. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">ADAM represents its non-hormonal implant approach. Both aim to expand contraceptive choice for men. Commercial strategy remains under evaluation. Regulatory approval remains the key milestone. The company is focused on clinical advancement first. Market entry will follow successful trials.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/contraline-raises-92-5m/" data-wpel-link="internal">Contraline Raises $92.5 Million Series B to Advance NES/T Male Contraceptive Development</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
